  <description><![CDATA[<p>A modern, contemporary take on a traditional alpine ski chalet, Secret de Neige provides beauty and comfort both inside and out. We're certain you'll fall in love with this chalet, with it's unique, quirky décor and it's elevated south-facing terrace where you'll find good views of the mountains day and night. Providing access to a heated ski room and a well deserved sauna, Chalet Secret de Neige doesn't need to try hard to tick all the right boxes. </p>
<h2>Ideal for groups </h2>
<p>With 6 bedrooms and the possibility to accommodate up to 14 people, invite your family - and your friends - to spend the week here. The attractive lounge area invites for socialising and relaxation after an active day on the runs. Due to it's large size, Secret de Neige is the ideal if you and your party are looking to spend quality time together away from home. Chalet Secret de Neige <span><span class="ui-provider a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak">is available to book exclusively as well as room by room.</span></span></p>
<h2>Perfect location</h2>
<p>If you like hitting the slopes as early as possible and getting back in time for the après ski, you'll benefit choosing this catered ski chalet. Located 100 metres from the ski lifts and 150 metres from the busy and appealing resort centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/acff50eb9ad84862a464f68b551bc497" href="/{localLink:umb://document/acff50eb9ad84862a464f68b551bc497}" title="Alpe d'Huez">Alpe d'Huez</a>, you'll be right in the heart of all the action. </p>
<h2>Relaxation facilities </h2>
<p>Make the most of the outdoors and enjoy breakfast on the large south-facing terrace, that is sure to get a lot of sunshine - alternatively, you can enjoy a glass of wine here in the evening and watch the sunset over the mountain peaks. </p>
<h3>Why is this and Inghams' Choice property?</h3>
<p><strong>Great for large groups</strong> - This catered ski chalet is an excellent choice if you and your group are looking to have a space to call your own on your ski holiday. The chalet provides everything you'll need for a week in the mountains, including a sauna and heated ski and boot room.</p>
<p><strong>Ideal location</strong> - Secret de Neige allows you to maximise your time on the slopes as it is located a short distance from the ski lifts and the resort centre of Alpe d'Huez.</p>
<p><strong>Modern design</strong> - Chalet Secret de Neige is a 4.5 star for good reason. Finished to an exceptionally high standard, the interior is a contemporary take on a traditional French wooden chalet.</p>
<h3><span>Our chalets are going greener, so our mountains don't</span></h3>
<p>Our menu is changing for the better. In all of our chalets we're giving you more choice, with both meat-free and meat options on offer throughout your stay. This is driven as part of our commitment to reduce our <a rel="noopener" data-udi="umb://document/67e40dbb55ff45098496ea2e7eee1f72" href="/{localLink:umb://document/67e40dbb55ff45098496ea2e7eee1f72}" target="_blank" title="Sustainability">carbon footprint</a>.</p>]]></description>
